    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. But what about the economic arguments? A lot of people are saying it's basically just a regressive tax that hurts people who can't afford to live in the city or don't have easy transit options. Is there a way to reconcile that with the environmental benefits, or are those two goals just fundamentally at odds?",
