      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The argument that congestion pricing is a regressive tax is a widely circulated, but ultimately political, talking point that overlooks the necessary trade-offs for a sustainable future. The solution isn't to abandon the pricing, but to rigorously dedicate the revenue to subsidizing transit passes and improving service in underserved communities. If the system is designed correctly, the environmental necessity of reducing emissions outweighs the perceived burden on those who can afford to adapt.",
